The paper discusses a framework for information extraction from the web, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of regular expressions and dictionaries suggests a focus on Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The mention of "web-scale" and "large scale" extraction indicates a need for efficient and scalable algorithms, which could fall under Databases (cs.DB). The use of unsupervised learning techniques suggests a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
